PostGreSQL database:
Go to http://www.postgresql.org/ftp/, select your distribution, download the appropriate package and proceed to installation according to PostGreSQL manual.
All supplementary required documentation can be found at http://www.postgresql.org/docs/manuals/

Firebird database:
Go to http://sourceforge.net/projects/firebird/files/, select your distribution, download the appropriate package and proceed to installation according to Firebird manual.
In case of a Linux server, follow instructions from "Firebird: Installing and Configuring Superclassic on Linux" file
All supplementary required documentation can be found at http://www.firebirdsql.org/en/reference-manuals/